item.title: Menu
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
[vc_row css=".vc_custom_1445604001830{padding-top: 150px !important;padding-bottom: 150px !important;}"][vc_column][vc_column_text css_animation="bottom-to-top"]

MENU

[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css_animation="bottom-to-top"]

Far far away, behind the word mountains, far from the countries Vokalia and Consonantia, there live the blind texts. Separated they live in Bookmarksgrove right at the coast of the Semantics.

[/vc_column_text][vc_row_inner css=".vc_custom_1445604387705{padding-top: 50px !important;}"][vc_column_inner width="1/3"][vc_single_image image="27" img_size="full" alignment="center" css_animation="left-to-right"][vc_column_text css_animation="left-to-right"]

THAI SOUP SEN JAN

[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css_animation="left-to-right" css=".vc_custom_1446122351617{margin-top: -30px !important;}"]

Tender noodles coupled with chicken broth, all with succulent pieces of chicken, shitake mushrooms and a simmered egg

[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css_animation="left-to-right" css=".vc_custom_1446045328539{margin-top: -30px !important;margin-bottom: 30px !important;}"]

$10

[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width="1/3"][vc_single_image image="28" img_size="full" alignment="center" css_animation="bottom-to-top"][vc_column_text css_animation="bottom-to-top"]

CHICKEN NOODLE SOUP

[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css_animation="bottom-to-top" css=".vc_custom_1446122299899{margin-top: -30px !important;}"]

The tom yum paste is hot, so try the soup before adding the chile and decide if any extra heat is required.

[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css_animation="bottom-to-top" css=".vc_custom_1446122327792{margin-top: -30px !important;margin-bottom: 30px !important;}"]

$11

[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width="1/3"][vc_single_image image="29" img_size="full" alignment="center" css_animation="right-to-left"][vc_column_text css_animation="right-to-left"]

COCONUT SOUP

[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css_animation="right-to-left" css=".vc_custom_1446122407255{margin-top: -30px !important;}"]

Authentic, bold, and delicious Thai flavors make this soup irresistible! This is the best Thai coconut soup I've had.

[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css_animation="right-to-left" css=".vc_custom_1446122412474{margin-top: -30px !important;margin-bottom: 30px !important;}"]

$10

[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner css=".vc_custom_1445604387705{padding-top: 50px !important;}"][vc_column_inner width="1/3"][vc_single_image image="30" img_size="full" alignment="center" css_animation="left-to-right"][vc_column_text css_animation="left-to-right"]

DUCK LEGS IN GREEN CURRY

[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1446122549344{margin-top: -30px !important;}"]

A delicious sweet and spicy soup perfect on a cold winter night. Best served with a loaf of crusty bread.

[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css_animation="left-to-right" css=".vc_custom_1446122556070{margin-top: -30px !important;margin-bottom: 30px !important;}"]

$11

[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width="1/3"][vc_single_image image="31" img_size="full" alignment="center" css_animation="bottom-to-top"][vc_column_text css_animation="bottom-to-top"]

TOM KA GAI

[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css_animation="bottom-to-top" css=".vc_custom_1446122613164{margin-top: -30px !important;}"]

Fragrant, spicy, and absolutely delicious Thai chicken soup. I've eaten a bit of Thai, and I think this comes very close.

[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css_animation="bottom-to-top" css=".vc_custom_1446122618909{margin-top: -30px !important;margin-bottom: 30px !important;}"]

$12

[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width="1/3"][vc_single_image image="32" img_size="full" alignment="center" css_animation="right-to-left"][vc_column_text css_animation="right-to-left"]

THAI GINGER SOUP

[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css_animation="right-to-left" css=".vc_custom_1446122674572{margin-top: -30px !important;}"]

A simple coconut milk base with chicken breast strips, ginger and cilantro. Garnish with red chilies and cilantro sprigs.

[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css_animation="right-to-left" css=".vc_custom_1446122682264{margin-top: -30px !important;margin-bottom: 30px !important;}"]

$11

[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner css=".vc_custom_1445604387705{padding-top: 50px !important;}"][vc_column_inner width="1/3"][vc_single_image image="33" img_size="full" alignment="center" css_animation="left-to-right"][vc_column_text css_animation="left-to-right"]

TOM YUM KOONG SOUP

[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css_animation="left-to-right" css=".vc_custom_1446122792163{margin-top: -30px !important;}"]

Galangal, a member of the ginger family, is a knobby root that tastes like a cross between ginger and pepper.

[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css_animation="left-to-right" css=".vc_custom_1446122797354{margin-top: -30px !important;margin-bottom: 30px !important;}"]

$12

[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width="1/3"][vc_single_image image="34" img_size="full" alignment="center" css_animation="bottom-to-top"][vc_column_text css_animation="bottom-to-top"]

THAI PUMPKIN SOUP

[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css_animation="bottom-to-top" css=".vc_custom_1446122963304{margin-top: -30px !important;}"]

This is a spicy Thai variety on our favorite pumpkin soup. Instead of the sour cream, this recipe uses coconut cream.

[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css_animation="bottom-to-top" css=".vc_custom_1446122852997{margin-top: -30px !important;margin-bottom: 30px !important;}"]

$13

[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width="1/3"][vc_single_image image="35" img_size="full" alignment="center" css_animation="right-to-left"][vc_column_text css_animation="right-to-left"]

SPICY CHICKEN SOUP

[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css_animation="right-to-left" css=".vc_custom_1446122987729{margin-top: -30px !important;}"]

A chunky hearty soup with a great blend of spices to warm you right to the bone. You can also add bean sprouts

[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css_animation="right-to-left" css=".vc_custom_1446122932924{margin-top: -30px !important;margin-bottom: 30px !important;}"]

$12

[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row]
